heaviest_rainfall.status: 23.86mm of rain was recorded as having fallen today, marking an exceptional precipitation event and it ranked 7th out of our records.  A rate of 8.3mm per hour was recorded during the 31.0 hour long storm.  The heaviest total rainfall occurred on 09 November 2025, dropping 47.89mm of rain over the 144.8 hour storm duration with a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 2nd for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 27.6mm per hour sustained for 2.6 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 6.1mm.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 34.3mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 31.0 hours; it delivered 23.86mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
